Hesai leverages millions of units in volume --", "id_str": "2075933828972265974", "in_reply_to_screen_name": "CoffeeStocksGuy", "in_reply_to_status_id_str": "2066925896485806228", "in_reply_to_user_id_str": "1425501982320701442", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 0, "retweet_count": 0, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "1281798858427691008"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [0, 5], "text": "HSAI"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNzU5MzM4Mjg4OTY3NTE2MTY=", "media": {"inline_media": []}, "richtext": {"richtext_tags": []}, "text": "$HSAI operates on a completely different scale and cost curve than Western peers like Ouster. While regulatory moats like the SAFE LiDAR Act protect US domestic production, they do not resolve uncompetitive Western cost structures.

Hesai leverages millions of units in volume -- achieving a commanding 43% global ADAS market share with dominant EV players like Xiaomi and Li Auto -- to fund continuous, chip-level R&D. By integrating complex components onto proprietary Silicon Photonics  and SoC architectures, Hesai has successfully driven unit costs down to an unmatched $150 -- $200 benchmark while maintaining strong 40% gross margins and positive net income. Furthermore, its massive expansion into global Level 3 autonomy (e.g., Mercedes-Benz) and the explosive physical AI/robotics market (partner with Nvidia) ensures robust growth entirely independent of US automotive procurement."}}}, "rest_id": "2075933828972265974", "source": "<a href="https://mobile.twitter.com" rel="nofollow">Twitter Web App</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "79", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}
